article.headline: Bryant 42, Stonehill 7
article.story: SMITHFIELD, R.I. -- Jordan Brown rushed for 228 yards and three touchdowns to lead Bryant to a 42-7 rout over Stonehill on Saturday. Brown, who finished with 26 carries, scored on runs of 2, 1 and 58 yards for the Bulldogs (4-2). His final touchdown of the game gave Bryant a 28-0 lead early in the third quarter. Brown amassed 269 all-purpose yards, becoming the second player in Bryant history with 4,000 all-purpose yards in a career (4,107). Stonehill, a Division II team, struggled to contain Brown and Bryant's offensive surge that totaled 476 yards. Ricardo McCray finished with 72 yards rushing on 12 carries and had a touchdown for Bryant. Mike Croce completed 7 of 13 passes for 147 yards, one touchdown and two interceptions. Stonehill quarterback Jesse Hunt threw for 221 yards and one touchdown, completing 12 of his 28 passes.
